If a player was unranked on a certain website, he was given the rank equivalent to the total number of players that were ranked on at least one website (that ranked as many players).
For example, if a player was unranked on Bleacher Report's top 50 prospects list, then he was given the rank of 64, which is the number of players that appeared in the top 50 of at least one wesbite.
